
- graphical user interface - gui
-gui  is a design scheme for computer interfaces that makes using a personal computer much more intuitive and user-friendly.
-Macintosh, released in 1984, was the first computer to use a GUI and mouse.
Desktop Metaphor, in which the computer's 2D screen is treated like a desktop, was developed at Xerox PARC in the early 1970s.


- GUI) is a design approach in which a computer's user interface is represented as a series of graphical objects on a screen.
-first GUIs were built on top of the DOS operating system, which was not designed to support GUIs, but after Windows 3.1 was released, Microsoft began to develop a new GUI called Windows 95.
-Windows 95 introduced many GUI elements that are still used in Windows versions today the start menu, taskbar, and Windows Explorer file manager.
